        <div class="accordion-container seo con-block max-width-10-desktop" data-block-status="loaded" data-block=""><div class="descr-list accordion foreground" id="accordion-1" role="presentation"><div role="heading" aria-level="3" class="descr-term"><button type="button" id="accordion-1-trigger-1" class="accordion-trigger tracking-header" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion-1-content-1" daa-ll="open-1--What kind of questions can I ask my PDF">
            What kind of questions can I ask my PDF?
          <span class="accordion-icon"></span></button></div><div aria-labelledby="accordion-1-trigger-1" id="accordion-1-content-1" hidden="true" class="descr-details"><div>You can use the Acrobat AI Assistant tool to ask a PDF all kinds of questions. AI Assistant will then provide a quick answer, using natural language for easier understanding. For example, you can ask AI Assistant to list a document’s five most important points, or you can ask it to draft an email summarizing your document. Don’t know what to ask or what to expect from a PDF AI tool? Simply select one of the common questions suggested by AI Assistant.</div></div><div role="heading" aria-level="3" class="descr-term"><button type="button" id="accordion-1-trigger-2" class="accordion-trigger tracking-header" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion-1-content-2" daa-ll="open-2--Can I use the tool to chat with other types of documents">
            Can I use the tool to chat with other types of documents?
          <span class="accordion-icon"></span></button></div><div aria-labelledby="accordion-1-trigger-2" id="accordion-1-content-2" hidden="true" class="descr-details"><div>Yes, you can upload a PDF or any other supported document file. If you upload a Microsoft Word document (DOCX), PowerPoint presentation (PPTX), TXT file, or RTF file, the Acrobat online tool will convert the file format to PDF. Then sign in to ask your document questions and get quick answers.</div></div><div role="heading" aria-level="3" class="descr-term"><button type="button" id="accordion-1-trigger-3" class="accordion-trigger tracking-header" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion-1-content-3" daa-ll="open-3--What languages does the Adobe Acrobat AI chat tool support">
            What languages does the Adobe Acrobat AI chat tool support?
          <span class="accordion-icon"></span></button></div><div aria-labelledby="accordion-1-trigger-3" id="accordion-1-content-3" hidden="true" class="descr-details"><div>Currently, Adobe Acrobat Al Assistant supports PDFs and documents in English, Japanese, French, German, Italian, Spanish, and Portuguese, with additional languages to be added in future releases. With translation capabilities, you can chat with your documents using original content from or to any of these languages. Al Assistant may inadvertently provide responses in languages other than English, Japanese, French, German, Italian, Spanish, and Portuguese, but these go beyond the intended purpose of the Al Assistant capability and should not be relied upon at this time.</div></div><div role="heading" aria-level="3" class="descr-term"><button type="button" id="accordion-1-trigger-4" class="accordion-trigger tracking-header" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion-1-content-4" daa-ll="open-4--Can I verify the information in the answers">
            Can I verify the information in the answers?
          <span class="accordion-icon"></span></button></div><div aria-labelledby="accordion-1-trigger-4" id="accordion-1-content-4" hidden="true" class="descr-details"><div>You’ll notice that many AI Assistant answers provide attribution by including numbered references as clickable links. When you select one of the numbered links in the AI Assistant chat answer, the AI PDF tool instantly highlights the related source content in your document. This interactive artificial intelligence feature provides a fast, seamless way for users to verify information with a single click. You can copy the chat history and use the answers to craft other content like emails, social posts, or presentations. <a href="https://helpx.adobe.com/acrobat/using/data-usage-and-handling.html">Learn more</a> about how the chat history is stored.</div></div><div role="heading" aria-level="3" class="descr-term"><button type="button" id="accordion-1-trigger-5" class="accordion-trigger tracking-header" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion-1-content-5" daa-ll="open-5--What is the best AI assistant for documents">
            What is the best AI assistant for documents?
          <span class="accordion-icon"></span></button></div><div aria-labelledby="accordion-1-trigger-5" id="accordion-1-content-5" hidden="true" class="descr-details"><div>Adobe Acrobat is one of the best AI assistants for documents. This AI document assistant is designed to help users chat with PDFs and other documents, allowing you to ask questions, compare files, review content, and extract key information.</div></div><div role="heading" aria-level="3" class="descr-term"><button type="button" id="accordion-1-trigger-6" class="accordion-trigger tracking-header" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion-1-content-6" daa-ll="open-6--How can I ask questions and get answers from my PDF">
            How can I ask questions and get answers from my PDF?
          <span class="accordion-icon"></span></button></div><div aria-labelledby="accordion-1-trigger-6" id="accordion-1-content-6" hidden="true" class="descr-details"><div>With Adobe Acrobat’s PDF chat tool, you can ask questions and get answers directly from your PDF in seconds, without reading the entire document.</div></div><div role="heading" aria-level="3" class="descr-term"><button type="button" id="accordion-1-trigger-7" class="accordion-trigger tracking-header" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion-1-content-7" daa-ll="open-7--Can I summarize individual sections of a PDF document">
            Can I summarize individual sections of a PDF document?
          <span class="accordion-icon"></span></button></div><div aria-labelledby="accordion-1-trigger-7" id="accordion-1-content-7" hidden="true" class="descr-details"><div>To summarize an individual section of a PDF document, upload a file to the Acrobat AI chat tool and sign in. Then ask your PDF to draft a summary of the specific section you need summarized. You can also ask other research questions, including questions that analyze data across tables shared in the document.</div></div><div role="heading" aria-level="3" class="descr-term"><button type="button" id="accordion-1-trigger-8" class="accordion-trigger tracking-header" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion-1-content-8" daa-ll="open-8--What is the best AI tool to compare documents">
            What is the best AI tool to compare documents?
          <span class="accordion-icon"></span></button></div><div aria-labelledby="accordion-1-trigger-8" id="accordion-1-content-8" hidden="true" class="descr-details"><div>Adobe Acrobat AI Assistant uses AI to compare documents, helping users identify differences, changes, and important updates across files, making it one of the best tools to quickly compare documents.</div></div><div role="heading" aria-level="3" class="descr-term"><button type="button" id="accordion-1-trigger-9" class="accordion-trigger tracking-header" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion-1-content-9" daa-ll="open-9--Is AI Assistant a secure tool to use to chat with PDFs">
            Is AI Assistant a secure tool to use to chat with PDFs?
          <span class="accordion-icon"></span></button></div><div aria-labelledby="accordion-1-trigger-9" id="accordion-1-content-9" hidden="true" class="descr-details"><div>
              <p>Security is paramount to Adobe. When you upload documents using this tool, they will be deleted from our servers to respect your privacy if you don’t sign in. Security measures are also built into every PDF created with Acrobat.</p>
              <p>In addition, Adobe has integrated the trusted Microsoft Azure OpenAI Service AI model with our proprietary technologies to provide generative AI capability in Acrobat. Adobe and its service providers do not use Adobe customer content to train the large language models (LLMs) — ours or a third party’s — that deliver Acrobat generative AI capabilities. We also do not permit third parties to manually review Adobe customer content.</p>
            </div></div><div role="heading" aria-level="3" class="descr-term"><button type="button" id="accordion-1-trigger-10" class="accordion-trigger tracking-header" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion-1-content-10" daa-ll="open-10--What is the best way to review documents">
            What is the best way to review documents?
          <span class="accordion-icon"></span></button></div><div aria-labelledby="accordion-1-trigger-10" id="accordion-1-content-10" hidden="true" class="descr-details"><div>One of the best ways to review documents is with our PDF chat tool which functions as an AI document reviewer that helps you analyze documents for accuracy, completeness, and key insights.</div></div><div role="heading" aria-level="3" class="descr-term"><button type="button" id="accordion-1-trigger-11" class="accordion-trigger tracking-header" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion-1-content-11" daa-ll="open-11--Can I chat with my PDF to analyze documents and extract key information">
            Can I chat with my PDF to analyze documents and extract key information?
          <span class="accordion-icon"></span></button></div><div aria-labelledby="accordion-1-trigger-11" id="accordion-1-content-11" hidden="true" class="descr-details"><div>Yes. Adobe Acrobat AI Assistant lets you chat with your PDF to analyze PDFs and extract key information such as facts, figures, clauses, and insights.</div></div></div></div>
